{
  "stem": "26609.6",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they would probably survive there, but they didn't, because, eh, a boy who worked for that priest, um, in the sheds with cows, or something-- I don't know how they called them-- he noticed once that the priest-- or his wife, I don't know who-- took some food [INAUDIBLE] down to the cellar.",
      "word_count": 54
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "He understood that there were hidden Jews, so he went over to the Gestapo and told them.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 34,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The Gestapo came and took them out, all of them.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But the ghetto was still there, so they took them to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my little brother-- Grodek was a small town, a very pretty town.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "There was, eh, the center of the little city, a square center in the middle of the city.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they called out all non-Jews around, put them around.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "They stood around, hundreds of them.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And in the center, they put my little brother.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Yes, and my mother had to stay-- including my mother, had to be there too.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "She had to-- they made her watch what they did.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And they hit my brother, that little boy of 13-- he was a bar mitzvah then.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He should have been.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "They hit him.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They beat him so hard, until he was a mass-- mess of blood.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "He fell.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And my mother said he still screamed mama.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 8 SECONDS] And she couldn't avert her eyes, because they made her look.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "If she looked away, they turned her head to see what they are doing.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I don't know what happened.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 35,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "I think his bones must be somewhere there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 36,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "That was, I think, in '41, or end of '41, because the Russians were '39, '40, till '41.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
